Three vertical tunnels~
The huge hall ends here, but three doorways in the west wall lead further
into this (tomb) building.  You inspect each doorway and to your amazement
you see that they are not rooms as you thought, but vertical tunnels.  In
each tunnel a ladder, of stone of course, is attached to the wall.  You look
up and down in all three tunnels seeing one open doorway further up in one
of them.  Otherwise you see but darkness.  You think you can make it up the
ladder to the single doorway, but you cannot be sure.  As if to point
something out, the wind hits the doorway with stronger force than ever, as
if it wanted to tear down the wall and get inside.  
