Path beside the Stonebridge~
You stand on a path beside the bridge.  You are shocked to see that it
seems to be a path made by living things...  But it is made out of stone. 
Who could have made this?  The stone in the path has crumbled in some
places, making it very dangerous to climb.  Looking downwards you see that
even the bottom where you assume the river once flowed is made out of stone.
Could it be that someone or something built a place entirely out of stone? 
You are not sure if you want to know the answer, and concentrate on deciding
whether you can make it down this path or not.  
